by%20ChatGPT%2C%26quot%3B%20Volberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBullets%20over%20bona%20fides%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20conventional%20approach%20of%20stuffing%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20with%20bolded%20job%20titles%2C%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20and%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsking%20applicants%20to%20summarize%20the%20value%20they%20would%20bring%20by%20sharing%20vignettes%20of%20success%20can%20elevate%20technical%20accomplishment%20over%20pedigree%20or%20background%2C%20she%20said.%20It's%20an%20example%20of%20what%20some%20HR%20types%20call%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-tests-impact-on-resume-and-employment-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eskills-based%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20no-frills%20call%20for%20applicants%20appears%20to%20build%20on%20his%20prior%20statements%20about%20being%20open%20to%20candidates%20from%20nontraditional%20backgrounds.%20For%20years%2C%20the%20billionaire%20has%20said%20that%20people%20didn't%20need%20a%20college%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-no-college-degree-needed-to-work-at-tesla-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edegree%20to%20work%20for%20Tesla%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Musk%20has%20said%20that%20he's%20more%20focused%20on%20evidence%20of%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%26quot%3B%20ability%20or%20achievement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20requested%20bullet%20points%20in%202025%20when%20he%20oversaw%20efforts%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20group%20to%20remake%20swaths%20of%20the%20US%20federal%20government.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20nearly%20year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FDOGE%2Fstatus%2F1883636068647342141%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20DOGE%20was%20seeking%20%26quot%3Bworld-class%26quot%3B%20software%20engineers%2C%20product%20managers%2C%20and%20data%20scientists%2C%20among%20other%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20application%20portal%20linked%20to%20the%20post%20contains%20a%20field%20instructing%20applicants%20to%20include%20two%20or%20three%20bullets%20%26quot%3Bshowcasing%20exceptional%20ability%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20to%20upload%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229273ee03-2140-47cc-be34-197daf148a94%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20focus%20on%20outcomes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVolberg%20said%20the%20bullet%20method%20is%20similar%20to%20guidance%20that%20her%20company%20already%20gives%20job%20seekers%3A%20Focus%20less%20on%20adjectives%20and%20more%20on%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20hiring%20manager's%20perspective%2C%20she%20said%2C%20the%20central%20question%20is%20whether%20a%20candidate%20can%20make%20their%20job%20easier%20by%20solving%20real%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20corollary%2C%20Volberg%20said%2C%20is%20fakers%20beware%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20say%20that%20you've%20solved%20these%20three%20things%2C%20you'd%20better%20be%20able%20to%20talk%20about%20them%20in%20detail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20it's%20often%20immediately%20clear%20to%20tech%20recruiters%20whether%20someone%20has%20actually%20done%20the%20work%20they%20describe.%20Candidates%20who%20exaggerate%20or%20fabricate%20their%20accomplishments%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20found%20out%20%E2%80%94%20and%20potentially%20blacklisted%2C%20Volberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22befd569b-d5d9-4e1d-8ad2-3321f5e9b88b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBullets%20might%20not%20work%20for%20everyone%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20candidate%20chicanery%2C%20there%20could%20be%20other%20risks%20to%20Musk's%20strategy%2C%20said%20David%20Murray%2C%20CEO%20of%20Confirm%2C%20a%20San%20Francisco%20startup%20focused%20on%20reinventing%20performance%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsking%20people%20to%20submit%20summaries%20of%20their%20greatest%20tech%20wins%20could%20mean%20that%20an%20employer%20like%20Tesla%20misses%20out%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonality-hire-introvert-extrovert-ai-work-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equiet%20contributors%20and%20introverts%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20might%20not%20do%20as%20good%20a%20job%20promoting%20themselves%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Bullets%20of%20key%20achievements%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0even%20more%20than%20with%20a%20typical%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0require%20people%20to%20make%20the%20case%20for%20their%20own%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurray%20said%20that%20Musk's%20approach%20also%20overlooks%20the%20impacts%20of%20the%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F13-signs-that-youre-smarter-than-you-think-you-are-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDunning-Kruger%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20people%20who%20aren't%20great%20at%20something%20tend%20to%20overestimate%20their%20abilities%2C%20and%20those%20who%20are%20ace%20might%20assume%20a%20task%20is%20easy%20for%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20he%20is%20asking%20people%20to%20do%20is%20to%20market%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20your%20career%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atparadis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etparadis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-approach-to-hiring-at-tesla-bullets-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1769077981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fdb8a73c910a400192e813b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-approach-to-hiring-at-tesla-bullets-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tesla's%20Elon%20Musk%20is%20asking%20job%20applicants%20to%20share%20t