0but%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20coming.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20background%2C%20his%20AI%20company%20has%20been%20gearing%20up%20to%20make%20that%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20quietly%20built%20up%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhumanoid-robot-companies-us-tesla-figure-1x-agility-apptronik-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehumanoid%20robotics%20lab%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20insiders%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20program%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20lab%20operates%20out%20of%20the%20same%20building%20as%20the%20company's%20finance%20team%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20employs%20around%20100%20data%20collectors.%20They're%20teaching%20a%20robotic%20arm%20how%20to%20perform%20household%20tasks%20as%20a%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20effort%20to%20build%20a%20humanoid%20robot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20explored%20robotics%20during%20its%20early%20years%20and%20built%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Fsolving-rubiks-cube%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erobotic%20hand%3C%2Fa%3E%20capable%20of%20solving%20a%20Rubik's%20Cube.%20The%20company%20closed%20the%20project%20in%202020%3B%20a%20company%20spokesperson%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20it%20had%20chosen%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fventurebeat.com%2Fbusiness%2Fopenai-disbands-its-robotics-research-team%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erefocus%20the%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20other%20projects.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inner%20workings%20of%20the%20new%20robotics%20lab%20haven't%20been%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20person%20with%20knowledge%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20the%20company%20is%20working%20on%20several%20new%20hardware%20projects%2C%20including%20robotics%2C%20that%20are%20in%20the%20early%20phases%20of%20development%2C%20and%20so%20far%2C%20none%20are%20core%20to%20the%20company's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20OpenAI%20put%20out%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Fstrengthening-the-us-ai-supply-chain%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequest%20for%20proposals%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20companies%20that%20manufacture%20in%20the%20US%20that%20could%20act%20as%20partners%20for%20the%20company's%20push%20into%20consumer%20devices%2C%20robotics%2C%20and%20cloud%20data%20centers.%20The%20company%20did%20not%20specify%20how%20much%20it%20intends%20to%20spend%20or%20provide%20a%20timeframe%20for%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20OpenAI%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lab%20has%20more%20than%20quadrupled%20in%20size%20since%20it%20launched%20in%20February%202025%2C%20insiders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20the%20company%20told%20employees%20it%20plans%20to%20open%20a%20second%20lab%20in%20Richmond%2C%20California.%20A%20December%20job%20posting%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Brobotics%20operator%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20company's%20contracting%20agency%20lists%20Richmond%20as%20the%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lab%20has%20a%20humanoid%20robot%20that%20multiple%20people%20described%20as%20%26quot%3BiRobot-like%26quot%3B%20on%20display%2C%20but%20the%20bot%20is%20mostly%20collecting%20dust%2C%20and%20few%20have%20seen%20it%20in%20operation.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20work%20in%20the%20lab%20is%20focused%20on%20teleoperating%20robotic%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-optimus-humanoid-robot-training-elon-musk-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edata%20collectors%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%203-D%20printed%20controllers%2C%20called%20GELLOs%2C%20to%20operate%20two%20Franka%20robots.%20These%20metal%20arms%20have%20pincers%20at%20the%20end%20and%20perform%20household%20tasks%20like%20putting%20bread%20in%20a%20toaster%20or%20folding%20laundry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20robots%20are%20made%20by%20Franka%2C%20a%20German%20robotics%20research%20company.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69714722a645d1188187c23a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20robots%20are%20made%20by%20Franka%2C%20a%20German%20robotics%20research%20company.%3Cp%3EFriso%20Gentsch%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20data%20collection%20program%20began%20in%20February%2C%20work%20focused%20on%20teaching%20the%20Franka%20robot%20how%20to%20put%20a%20rubber%20duck%20in%20a%20cup.%20Since%20then%2C%20it%20has%20shifted%20to%20increasingly%20more%20sophisticated%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20lab%20offers%20a%20rare%20glimpse%20into%20how%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-power-list-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einfluential%20AI%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20approaching%20robotics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompetitors%20like%20Tesla%20put%20on%20flashy%20demos%20and%20often%20train%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-optimus-humanoid-robot-training-elon-musk-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efull%20humanoid%20robots%3C%2Fa%3E%20controlled%20by%20motion%20capture%20suits%20and%20virtual%20reality%20headsets.%20OpenAI%20is%20taking%20a%20quieter%20path%2C%20scaling%20contractor-driven%20data%20collection%20to%20train%20robotic%20arms%20on%20basic%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20approaches%20show%20how%20far%20leading%20AI%20companies%20remain%20from%20building%20functional%20household%20robots%2C%20and%20how%20much%20of%20that%20work%20still%20relies%20on%20human%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b46d58c-65fe-4fa1-8f1a-d2018b3ecd04%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20race%20for%20data%3C%2F