g%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20You%20can%20hear%20our%20entire%20conversation%20on%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fchuck-klosterman-on-why-football-owns-tv-and-why-it%2Fid1080467174%3Fi%3D1000746016253%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChannels%3C%2Fa%3E%20podcast.%20What%20follows%20are%20edited%20excerpts%20from%20our%20chat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeter%20Kafka%3A%20What%20is%20the%20point%20of%20a%20book%20called%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc02e3d6ba8d298047a00ac86570703c98814ad28094ed69c1c18696dd797c255%26postID%3D69712aeca1e4d776a3685589%26postSlug%3Dfootball-chuck-klosterman-nfl-college-money-tv-interview-peter-kafka%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FFootball-Chuck-Klosterman%252Fdp%252F0593490649%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFootball%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%20in%202026%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChuck%20Klosterman%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20have%20been%20obsessed%20with%20sports%20and%20football%20my%20entire%20life.%20And%20probably%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20made%20an%20unspoken%2C%20abstract%20decision%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Eat%20some%20point%2C%20I%20want%20to%20do%20a%20book%20that's%20just%20about%20sports%3C%2Fem%3E.%20My%20initial%20idea%20was%20that%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20about%20basketball%2C%20but%20I%20realized%20that's%20crazy%3A%20If%20you're%20writing%20about%20something%20that's%20part%20of%20the%20culture%2C%20football%20is%20the%20sport.%20It's%20the%20only%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20someone%20said%20to%20you%2C%20%26quot%3BExplain%20the%20last%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%20through%20some%20idea%2C%20some%20metaphor%2C%26quot%3B%20football%20is%20the%20thing%20to%20pick.%20It%20might%20not%20be%20the%20case%20for%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20but%20it%20is%20for%20the%20end%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%20And%20it%20is%20for%20the%20world%20we%20live%20in%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20of%20the%20big%20changes%20in%20sports%20%E2%80%94%20and%20definitely%20in%20football%20%E2%80%94%20recently%20is%20the%20legalization%20of%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichael-lewis-sports-betting-podcast-peter-kafka-interview-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Esports%20betting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20It's%20omnipresent.%20You%20seem%20ambivalent-to-positive%20about%20it%2C%20which%20is%20not%20where%20I%20thought%20you'd%20end%20up.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECHUCK%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Do%20I%20think%20that%20gambling%20in%20this%20legalized%20way%20is%20bad%20for%20society%3F%20I%20would%20say%20%3Cem%3Eprobably%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20for%20all%20of%20the%20predictable%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20because%20it's%20on%20your%20phone%20and%20you've%20put%20your%20%5Bfinancial%20information%5D%20in%2C%20so%20the%20money%20does%20not%20seem%20real.%20Even%20if%20it%20was%20just%20a%20situation%20where%20you%20had%20to%20feed%20dollar%20bills%20into%20it%2C%20everything%20would%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou're%20taking%20something%20that's%20addictive%20for%20some%20people%20and%20marrying%20it%20to%20your%20phone%2C%20which%20is%20also%20addictive%20for%20some%20people.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Frecode%2F22947732%2Fphones-sports-betting-gambling-apple-google-march-madness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20seems%20like%20an%20obvious%20way%20to%20get%20in%20trouble%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECHUCK%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20But%20for%20football%2C%20it%20is%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it%20adds%20a%20different%20context%20for%20conversation%20about%20it.%20When%20I%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20other%20dads%2C%20we'll%20talk%20about%20sports%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20then%20there'll%20be%20this%20other%20conversation.%20About%20%3Cem%3Egambling%3C%2Fem%3E.%20We're%20still%20technically%20talking%20about%20%3Cem%3Efootball%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20this%20is%20a%20whole%20different%20thing.%20It%20has%20a%20different%20context%2C%20a%20different%20meaning.%20It%20says%20more%20about%20the%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20could%20argue%20that%20it's%20a%20weird%20argument%20for%20gambling%20being%20good.%20But%20if%20we%20look%20at%20football%20as%20a%20form%20of%20entertainment%2C%20a%20distraction%2C%20something%20to%20consume%2C%20to%20occupy%20yourself%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20gambling%20does%20make%20it%20more%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20is%20the%20pitch%20from%20the%20entire%20sports%20gambling%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20it%20improves%20the%20game%2C%20it%20adds%20stakes%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20more%20interesting.%20You%20seem%20to%20agree.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertainly%20there%20are%20people%20who%20feel%20that%20way.%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20I%20know%20who%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20gambling%2C%20they%20have%20a%20sort%20of%20mixed%20feelings%20about%20it%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20it%20does%20bother%20them%20that%20suddenly%20the%20game%20seems%20meaningless%20if%20they're%20not%20gambling%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20me%2C%20as%20somebody%20who%20doesn't%20really%20put%20money%20into%20it%2C%20I%20find%20it%20a%20fascinating%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%3A%20Indiana%20was%20an%20eight-and-a-half%20point%20favorite%20%5Bin%20Monday's%20college%20football%20championship%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FCollege_Football_Playoff_National_Championship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egame%3C%2Fa%3E%5D.%20They%20did%20not%20cover.%20But%20the%20meaning%20of%20eight-and-a-half%20points%20in%20a%20spread%20suggests%20that%20the%20gambling%20markets%20believe%20it%20will%20be%20a%20blowout.%20That's%20different%20than%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20Indiana's%20gonna%20win%20easily.%26quot%3B%20I%20find%20it%20to%20be%20much%20more%20intriguing%20than%20I%20would've%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20definitely%20against%20the%20idea%20of%20sports%20betting.%20Ideologically%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20bad.%26quot%3B%20And%20like%20I%20say%2C%20socially%20it%20probably%20is.%20But%20for%20each%20individual%20sport%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20argue%20that%20football's%20grip%20on%20America%20will%20eventually%20collapse.%20How%20will%20that%20happen%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFootball%20is%20not%20just%20the%20most%20popular%20thing%2C%20or%20just%20too%20big%20to%20fail.%20It%20is%20too%20big%20to%20stop%20expanding.%20It%20has%20to%20constantly%20get%20bigger.%20The%20financial%20demands%20of%20it%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20revenue%20it%20has%20to%20make%2C%20can%20only%20go%20up.%20The%20NFL%20only%20operates%20from%20the%20position%20of%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20we%20stretch%20out%20further%3F%20Can%20we%20even%20swallow%20up%20all%20the%20other%20sports%3F%20Can%20we%20expand%20into%20Europe%20and%20all%20of%20these%20things%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20right%20now%2C%20that's%20a%20successful%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20more%20they%20make%2C%20the%20more%20people%20consume%2C%20the%20more%20people%20spend%20on%20it%20%E2%80%94most%20importantly%2C%20the%20TV%20networks%20and%20streamers%20who%20need%20it.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20depth%20of%20caring%20is%20so%20deep.%20If%20football%20went%20away%20this%20fall%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20people%20will%20be%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20am%20I%20gonna%20bet%20on%3F%20What%20is%20my%20life%20gonna%20be%20like%3F%20Who%20am%20I%3F%20What's%20my%20identity%20if%20I'm%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20this%20team%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20really%20saw%20this%20during%20COVID.%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.si.com%2Fcollege%2F2021%2F01%2F11%2Fcollege-football-2020-season-covid-19-daily-cover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWe're%20still%20playing%20college%20football%3C%2Fa%3E.%20No%20one's%20in%20their%20classes%2C%20but%20we%20gotta%20play%20these%20games.%20We%20can't%20not%20play%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it's%20really%20brittle%2C%20right%3F%20It's%20a%20system%20that%20has%20to%20keep%20going.%20But%20I%20think%20at%20some%20point%20there%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20change.%20Probably%20in%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20that%20advertising%20is%20going%20to%20disappear.%20It's%20just%20that%20what%20it%20costs%20to%20buy%20an%20ad%20during%20a%20football%20game%20%E2%80%A6%20it's%20not%20going%20be%20worth%20the%20trade%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20let's%20say%20it%20gets%20to%20be%20a%20point%20when%20Fox%20or%20Amazon%20Prime%2C%20or%20whoever's%20carrying%20these%20games%2C%20renegotiates%20their%20NFL%20contract%20and%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20the%20number%20doesn't%20go%20up.%20Maybe%20even%20the%20number%20goes%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%5BThat%20puts%20the%5D%20NFL's%20in%20this%20weird%20position%20%E2%80%94%20they%20have%20to%20take%20their%20best%20offer.%20Then%20the%20players%20will%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20way%20we're%20going%20to%20take%20less%20money.%20There's%20no%20way%20we're%20going%20to%20start%20playing%2022%20games%20just%20because%20you're%20not%20making%20enough%20money%20from%20CBS.%20We're%20going%20to%20strike.%26quot%3B%20Or%20the%20owners%20will%20be%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20lock%20the%20players%20out%26quot%3B%20%5Bbecause%20they%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20them%5D%20%E2%80%94%20like%20what's%20happened%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2F2021%25E2%2580%259322_Major_League_Baseball_lockout%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebaseball%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20happened%20now%2C%20it%20would%20be%20this%20American%20calamity%2C%20where%20people%20would%20freak%20out.%20But%20as%20people%20have%20less%20and%20less%20of%20a%20personal%20relationship%20to%20the%20game%20when%20this%20happens%20in%20the%20future%2C%20they'll%20be%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20that's%20an%20entertaining%20distraction.%20I%20can%20replace%20it%20with%20something%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20has%20to%20be%20part%20of%20your%20life%20for%20it%20to%20be%20so%20important%20that%20you'll%20do%20whatever%20you%20can%20to%20keep%20it%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20will%20fans%20have%20less%20of%20a%20relationship%20to%20football%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comparison%20I%20use%20is%20horse%20racing.%20In%20the%201920s%2C%20along%20with%20boxing%20and%20baseball%2C%20it%20was%20the%20biggest%20sport.%20And%20in%20the%201920s%2C%20the%20average%20person%20still%20had%20a%20real%20relationship%20to%20the%20culture%20of%20horses.%20They%20had%20a%20blue-collar%20job%2C%20and%20horses%20were%20still%20doing%20some%20of%20the%20labor.%20Or%20their%20dad%20had%20a%20horse%20farm.%20They%20definitely%20saw%20horses%20all%20the%20time.%20The%20horse%20was%20part%20of%20the%20world%20in%20which%20they%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20case.%20Now%2C%20horse%20racing%20is%20just%20for%20people%20who%20own%20horses%20and%20people%20who%20gamble%20on%20it.%20That's%20really%20all%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20fear%20is%20that%20football's%20gonna%20put%20itself%20in%20a%20position%20where%20it's%20too%20big.%20Its%20tentacles%20reach%20too%20far.%20And%20people%20will%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20guess%20we'll%20choose%20something%20else.%26quot%3B%20And%20when%20it%20collapses%2C%20something%20that%20size%20collapses%20hard.%20It%20kind%20of%20implodes%20on%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20one%20of%20these%20people%20%5Bwho%20complain%20about%20capitalism%5D.%20But%20I%20do%20think%20some%20of%20the%20problems%20of%20capitalism%20are%20easiest%20seen%20through%20sports%20leagues%2C%20which%20are%20smaller%20simulations%20of%20society.%20And%20what's%20happening%20with%20the%20way%20money%20operates%20in%20pro%20and%20college%20football%2C%20it%20seems%20precarious%20to%20me.%20The%20financial%20side's%20changing%20in%20an%20exponential%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20society%20shifts%2C%20it's%20the%20big%20things%20that%20can't.%20They're%20not%20nimble.%20The%20small%20things%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffootball-chuck-klosterman-nfl-college-money-tv-interview-peter-kafka%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1769076361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69712c97d3c7faef0eccada2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffootball-chuck-klosterman-nfl-college-money-tv-interview-peter-kafka%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Writer%20Chuck%20Klosterman%20loves%20football%20%E2%80%94%20like%20most%20of%20America.%20But%20he%20thinks%20the%20sport's%20sheer%20size%20will%20ultimately%20be%20its%20demise.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pkafka%40insider.com%20(Peter%20Kafka)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffootball-chuck-klosterman-nfl-college-money-tv-interview-peter-kafka%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We're%20siblings%20who%20built%20a%206-figure%20Turo%20business%20in%20under%202%20years.%20We%20started%20with%20just%20our%20mom's%20car%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20here's%20how%20we%20scaled%20up.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22two%20siblings%20pose%20next%20to%20two%20black%20cars%20outside%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696fd8cbd3c7faef0ecc95f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMike%20and%20Darlene%20Person.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20JDM%20Whipz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESiblings%20Michael%20Rumph%20and%20Darlene%20Person%20built%20JDM%20Whipz%2C%20a%20profitable%20Turo%20car%20rental%20fleet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJDM%20Whipz%20grew%20to%2013%20vehicles%20in%20Atlanta%20by%20reinvesting%20profits%20and%20focusing%20on%20customer%20service.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20experience%20highlights%20Turo%20business%20strategies%2C%20challenges%2C%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20planning.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20conversations%20with%20Michael%20Rumph%2C%2060%2C%20and%20Darlene%20Person%2C%2061%2C%20siblings%20in%20metro%20Atlanta%20who%20run%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjdmwhipz.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJDM%20Whipz%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%2013-car%20Turo%20fleet.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDarlene%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20For%20several%20years%2C%20my%20brother%2C%20Mike%2C%20and%20I%20talked%20about%20wanting%20to%20go%20into%20business%20together.%20We%20considered%20a%20few%20ideas%20but%20hadn't%20settled%20on%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202022%2C%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturo-review-pros-and-cons-of-using-the-car-sharing-company-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erented%20an%20Escalade%20from%20Turo%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20family%20trip.%20Almost%20exactly%20a%20year%20later%2C%20we%20launched%20our%20own%20Turo%20business%2C%20JDM%20Whipz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202024%2C%20JDM%20Whipz%20was%20making%20six%20figures%20in%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273f7e4e1-f17f-4c9e-bc61-79bce6524d78%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20were%20fascinated%20by%20how%20quickly%20and%20easily%20we'd%20rented%20a%20car%20from%20Turo%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDarlene%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMike%20dove%20into%20research%2C%20sending%20me%20videos%20and%20